# ============================================
# ChosenWell - Environment Variables
# ============================================
# This file documents all environment variables needed for deployment
# ============================================

# ============================================
# NEON - PostgreSQL Database (Free Tier)
# ============================================
# Sign up at https://neon.tech (free)
# 
# Steps:
# 1. Create account at neon.tech
# 2. Create a new project (choose region: us-east-1 for best Railway performance)
# 3. Copy the connection string from the dashboard
#
# Connection string format:
# postgresql://username:password@ep-xxxx-xxxx.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@ep-xxxx.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require

# ============================================
# RAILWAY - Backend (Go)
# ============================================
# These variables are set in Railway Dashboard > Variables

# Backend Port (Railway sets PORT automatically - DO NOT SET MANUALLY)
# PORT is injected by Railway at runtime

# Frontend URL for CORS (your Vercel deployment URL)
# Add this to allow requests from your Vercel frontend
FRONTEND_URL=https://chosenwell.co.in
AI_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:8000
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=
RESEND_FROM_NAME=ChosenWell
RESEND_API_URL=https://api.resend.com
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite
GEMINI_TEMPERATURE=1.7

# ============================================
# VERCEL - Frontend (Next.js)
# ============================================
# Add these in Vercel Dashboard > Project Settings > Environment Variables

# Your production site URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://chosenwell.co.in

# Backend API URL (your Railway backend URL)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://chosenwell-production.up.railway.app

# Disable Next.js telemetry
NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT STEPS
# ============================================
#
# --- STEP 1: NEON (PostgreSQL Database) ---
# 1. Go to https://neon.tech and sign up (free)
# 2. Create a new project
#    - Name: chosenwell-db
#    - Region: us-east-1
# 3. Copy the connection string (includes ?sslmode=require)
#
# --- STEP 2: RAILWAY (Backend) ---
# 1. Go to https://railway.app and create a new project
# 2. Click "Deploy from GitHub repo" and select your repository
# 3. Configure:
#    - Root Directory: apps/backend
#    - Railway auto-detects Go and builds automatically
# 4. Add Environment Variables in Railway Dashboard > Variables:
#    - DATABASE_URL = (paste your Neon connection string)
#    - FRONTEND_URL = https://chosenwell.co.in
#    - AI_SERVICE_URL = http://your-langchain-service:8000
#    - RESEND_API_KEY = (your Resend API key)
#    - RESEND_FROM_EMAIL = (your verified Resend sender)
#    - GOOGLE_API_KEY = (your Google AI API key)
#    - (PORT is set automatically by Railway - don't add it)
# 5. Generate a domain: Settings > Networking > Generate Domain
# 6. Note your backend URL (e.g., https://chosenwell-api.up.railway.app)
#
# --- STEP 3: VERCEL (Frontend) ---
# 1. Go to https://vercel.com and import your GitHub repository
# 2. Configure:
#    - Root Directory: apps/frontend
#    - Framework Preset: Next.js (auto-detected)
# 3. Add Environment Variables:
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL = https://chosenwell.co.in
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL = https://your-app.up.railway.app (your Railway URL)
#    - NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED = 1
# 4. Deploy!
#
# --- STEP 4: Custom Domain (chosenwell.co.in) ---
# 1. In Vercel: Settings > Domains > Add chosenwell.co.in
# 2. Update DNS records at your domain registrar as instructed by Vercel
# 3. Vercel will auto-provision SSL certificate
#
# ============================================

